Deathrun_tyro, by knife and Roosta

About a week ago, I started to seriously get into deathrun. It turned out to be FAR more fun than I could have expected, and also felt like it is in area in which I could have a lot of fun mapping.

After seeing most of the better deathrun maps out there, I found that there wasn't really one that was actually all that good. On every map, there was at least one trap that would require someone to sacrifice themselves to let others pass. Thus, I, together with knife, set out to create a map with traps that would not require sacrifice. This would hopefully allow everyone to enjoy the map, rather than forcing an unlucky few to sit out for the inevitably long rounds.

Traps:
1-6 by Roosta:
1. Killer balancing beam. Fades to red, allowing CTs a time for response.
2. Rotating balancing beam. Beatable, but a skilled T can take out CTs.
3. Sequence of breakable floors. CTs try to get across while Ts try breaking the floor to stop them.
4. Break 1 of 3 floor panels in an attempt to drop CTs.
5. Boulder-dash. CTs try to get across path while Ts launch a boulder at them.
6. Stacked pushing walls. Ts try to push CTs off of walkway while CTs try to dodge the walls.

7-9 by knife:
7. 3x3 killer grid. Pushing buttons creates random set of killer squares.
8. Spinning floor blades. Bunny hop time!
9. Dropping roof panels. Ts try to squash the CTs

10-12 by Roosta:
10. Melon cannon. Ts try to kill CTs with melons.
11. Flipping floor panels. Ts try to drop the CTs to a lower level.
12. Longcat is LOOOOOOONG!

Overall, the project has been a success. I chose not to include a timer system due to the fact that the traps should not take forever; they should not, with experience, require sacrifice. They should, however, remain difficult for quite some time, and become more difficult with more skilled Ts. Enjoy!

Special thanks:
Teeth- Thanks for drinking all of my soda.
Shini- Thanks for the beta test!
intox. Triggs- Thanks for the helpfull criticism.
Have FUN!!!

DEATHRUN_TRIBUTE by Target Practice

- This is a deathrun map, with a twist.
- Features 18 traps, at least 9 of which have never been seen before in deathrun.
- After 4-minutes, players will be teleported to a volleyball room.
- There are 4 random rewards when completing the map.
- Give the bird a hug.

_________________________________________________

THIS MAP IS SPONSORED BY

Husky Gaming
www.huskygaming.com
DrivenByFear

_________________________________________________

VOLLEYBALL ROOM
...If those pesky CTs just don't die then settle the round with a friendly match of volleyball. 
...After four minutes, all living players will be teleported to the volleyball room.
...The team who reaches 2 points first, falls to a gruesome death.
...Terrorists have the advantage here due to their speed and duel pistols.

RANDOM REWARDS
...If you are lucky or skilled enough to complete this map, then you will not be dissappointed.
...This map incorporates a special win-system whereby upon completion you will be teleported to a random reward.
...These rewards are chosen randomly (duh?), and will greatly alter your gaming experience.

Random Reward 1: The laser room.

As a terrorist you must dodge the lasers and knife those CTs before they shoot you!

Random Reward 2: Shotgun justice.

Get shotgun. Kill Ts. Job done. End of.

Random Reward 3: P90 mayhem.

P90 + lots of ammo. You know the drill.

Random Reward 4: Breakfloor (My personal favourite).

Shoot the floor and get to the other side without causing too much mayhem...

_________________________________________________

- Many thanks go to DragonRock and Mapjunkies.
- Special thanks goes to Archangel for all his help, advice, and wisdom.
- Thanks to [UDEL]Steve for the traffic lights idea.
- Further thanks to Paper-Cut.
- I appreciate all the beta testers who took part in playing the private tests throughout the making of this map.
________________________________________________

INSTALLATION:

- To install the map you will need to copy&paste (or extract the contents of the .rar if you wish) the .BSP file (deathrun_tribute_final.bsp) into the 'maps' folder.
- To get to this folder you will need to go into:
- Program Files>Steam>Steamapps>counter-strike source>cstrike>maps.
- The .bsp file included in the download should go in your maps folder.
- Load up the game and you should be able to play it.
_________________________________________________

If you have any problems or queries about this map then feel free to contact me:

- xfire: targetpractice808
- STEAM Friends: Target Practice

Enjoy the map.

Almost all traps are new, and if they aren't, they are creatively new-made.

NAME EXPLANATIONL
synchronicity
    (sin'-krun-iss'-it-tee) n. 1: the relation that exists when events occur at the same time; simultaneity; synchronism. 2: coincidence of events that seem to be meaningfully related, conceived in Jungian theory as an explanatory principle on the level of causality; used especially for psychic events that are not explained by conventional mechanisms of causality. [from Greek syn- "same" + khronos "time."]

STORY:
Earth 2156 A.D.
After all the world's recourses have been depleted, the 2 big factions, west and east, go out to space to collect valuable minerals and water. Over the years, thousands of space stations were made. Now the earth is under attack by an alien race, out for more inhabitable planets. The aliens look exactly like humans but they have an unstoppable desire for blood.
Now they are trying to cut off the world’s recourses supply by taking over the stations, to stop them, the space stations started making special traps in their entrances to stop the aliens from taking over. Now it’s your job to stop them! So, pick up the custom gun and shoot it!
But be fast, the maximum number of players is 3. If you are too late, the timer is off, and you're dead!
